    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions achieving Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 — is accepted given the medium model risk level, the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (E/uval ≤ 1.44 in all cases), the dual-laboratory experimental dataset, and the corroborating evidence from the broader FEA ensemble. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
